The paper presents a novel evolutionary approach for the automatic generation of deep neural networks, which combines genetic algorithms with dynamic structured grammatical evolution. This work is primarily focused on the development of a new method for generating deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, the paper also discusses the performance of the generated networks on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the use of genetic algorithms and grammatical evolution could also place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
